        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "On MySQL binding in queries doesn't work right - when using Zend_Db_Table_Row->save() PDO exception occurs.\n{code:title=PDO exception}SQLSTATE[HY093]: Invalid parameter number: parameter was not defined.{code}\n\nBy digging into code i found out that bind array keys are not prefixed with ':', but this is required for PDO.\n\nI'm not sure if this fix will work well for all DB adapters.\n{code:title=Temporary fix: Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract->query}\n...\n\/\/ is the $sql a Zend_Db_Select object?\nif ($sql instanceof Zend_Db_Select) {\n\t$sql = $sql->__toString();\n}\n\/\/ Fix here\nif(!empty($bind)){\n\tforeach($bind as $k=>$v){\n\t\t$bind[\":$k\"] = $v;\n\t\tunset($bind[$k]);\n\t}\n}\n        \n\/\/ prepare and execute the statement with profiling\n$stmt = $this->prepare($sql);\n$q = $this->_profiler->queryStart($sql);\n$stmt->execute((array) $bind);\n$this->_profiler->queryEnd($q);\n...\n{code}"
        },
